    "title": "wallet: check descriptor cache xpub length before decoding",
    "user": {
      "login": "alhudz",
      "id": 50839256,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUwODM5MjU2",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/50839256?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/alhudz",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/alhudz",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alhudz/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alhudz/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alhudz/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alhudz/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alhudz/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alhudz/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alhudz/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alhudz/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alhudz/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "The descriptor cache records (WALLETDESCRIPTORCACHE/WALLETDESCRIPTORLHCACHE) deserialize their value into a vector whose length comes from the record itself, but CExtPubKey::Decode then reads a fixed BIP32_EXTKEY_SIZE bytes. A record encoding a shorter xpub makes Decode read past the vector (caught as a container-overflow under ASAN).\nReject records whose serialized xpub isn't exactly BIP32_EXTKEY_SIZE, the same way the other malformed records in this loader return DBErrors::CORRUPT.",
    "labels": [
